If you want dynamically query the form fields, you should wrap your form with [`Form.create`][1].

It injects useful functionalities like `onFieldsChange` listener:

```
const onFieldsChange = (_, changedFiels) =&gt; {
  const { username } = changedFiels;
  if (username) {
    // Make your API checks
    console.log(`Now changing ${username.name}`);
  }
};

const ValidatedFields = Form.create({ onFieldsChange })(App);
```

**Note:** You should keep your `Form.Item`s uncontrolled using [`getFieldDecorator`][2] therefore avoiding `onChange` while collecting form data.

If you still insist to make form items controlled, you should use [`getFieldValue`][1]:

```
const handleChange = e =&gt; {
  const { name, value } = e.target;
  const { getFieldValue } = form;

  setState(() =&gt; ({
    ...state,
    [name]: value
  }));

  // or use getFieldValue for a single query
  const values = getFieldsValue([&#39;formName&#39;,...more fields]);

  if (values.length) {
    // API CALL
  }
};
```

[![Edit Q-58289639-FormFieldValidate](https://codesandbox.io/static/img/play-codesandbox.svg)](https://codesandbox.io/s/q-58289639-formfieldvalidate-201tp?fontsize=14)


  [1]: https://ant.design/components/form/#Formcreate(options)
  [2]: https://ant.design/components/form/#thispropsformgetFieldDecorator(id,-options)

